AUDIENCE: So Di Fara.

01:03:06.460 --> 01:03:10.800
Often, if you don't get there
right at 11:30, and it's the

01:03:10.800 --> 01:03:13.494
weekend, you wait a long
time for your pizza.

01:03:13.494 --> 01:03:16.935
I have this notion that--
it's pretty good pizza.

01:03:16.935 --> 01:03:18.250
Don't get me wrong.

01:03:18.250 --> 01:03:20.625
But I have this notion that
people love it the way that

01:03:20.625 --> 01:03:22.540
they do because by the time
they get it, they're so

01:03:22.540 --> 01:03:24.592
hungry, and they've waited so
long, it's kind of like a

01:03:24.592 --> 01:03:25.732
pizza Stockholm Syndrome.

01:03:25.732 --> 01:03:26.644
SCOTT WIENER: Yes.

01:03:26.644 --> 01:03:27.890
AUDIENCE: Is there
anything to that?

01:03:27.890 --> 01:03:28.610
SCOTT WIENER: Oh,
without a doubt.

01:03:28.610 --> 01:03:31.610
Part of it is that when you go
to any place that has hype,

01:03:31.610 --> 01:03:33.750
that there's so much going on,
and you're looking around, you

01:03:33.750 --> 01:03:34.440
see all these people.

01:03:34.440 --> 01:03:36.310
When you're at Di Fara, there's
this amazing communal

01:03:36.310 --> 01:03:40.930
thing that happens where half
the people are there looking

01:03:40.930 --> 01:03:43.770
at the other half being like,
oh, it's your first time?

01:03:43.770 --> 01:03:44.640
I'll show you.

01:03:44.640 --> 01:03:45.150
That kind of thing.

01:03:45.150 --> 01:03:47.230
And then the other half are
like, oh, what do we do?

01:03:47.230 --> 01:03:47.720
Where do I go?

01:03:47.720 --> 01:03:49.490
It's smoky in here, and
my eyes are crying.

01:03:49.490 --> 01:03:51.120
What am I going to do?

01:03:51.120 --> 01:03:53.170
And I love watching
that whole scene.

01:03:53.170 --> 01:03:56.260
But the best way to approach
Di Fara is definitely not

01:03:56.260 --> 01:03:58.620
hungry, because you'll always
be hungry by the

01:03:58.620 --> 01:03:59.570
time it comes out.

01:03:59.570 --> 01:04:01.540
And if you're bringing somebody
there who's never

01:04:01.540 --> 01:04:03.110
been there, don't hype it up.

01:04:03.110 --> 01:04:04.870
Don't tell them anything.

01:04:04.870 --> 01:04:07.520
Sometimes I'll get tours of,
like, a family from Australia

01:04:07.520 --> 01:04:09.590
or something like that,
or from Texas.

01:04:09.590 --> 01:04:10.660
I had a family from Texas.

01:04:10.660 --> 01:04:12.770
They never heard anything
about it.

01:04:12.770 --> 01:04:13.600
I told them where to meet me.

01:04:13.600 --> 01:04:14.910
I said, meet me in front
of this place.

01:04:14.910 --> 01:04:15.860
I didn't say a word.

01:04:15.860 --> 01:04:18.400
And they ate it, and they were
able to kind of discover it

01:04:18.400 --> 01:04:20.620
for themselves, which
is kind of rare.

01:04:20.620 --> 01:04:22.590
It's rare around here to
find somebody who's

01:04:22.590 --> 01:04:24.060
never heard about it.

01:04:24.060 --> 01:04:26.610
At least there are myths going
around where people say, oh,

01:04:26.610 --> 01:04:28.705
what about that place where
there's that guy?

01:04:28.705 --> 01:04:32.050
And he only makes 10 pizzas
a day, or whatever.

01:04:32.050 --> 01:04:34.020
When you're going to a place
like Di Fara, or anything that

01:04:34.020 --> 01:04:38.210
has that hype, you just have to
bring those pretzels, bring

01:04:38.210 --> 01:04:39.810
those raisins.

01:04:39.810 --> 01:04:41.440
Or water.

01:04:41.440 --> 01:04:42.020
Water is good.

01:04:42.020 --> 01:04:43.650
When you're getting hungry, just
drink some of that water.

01:04:43.650 --> 01:04:45.560
And at Di Fara--

01:04:45.560 --> 01:04:47.490
this is probably the last thing
I should tell you guys,

01:04:47.490 --> 01:04:50.240
because I know you guys probably
have to work today.

01:04:50.240 --> 01:04:52.350
But I'm going to stay here
and eat all this.

01:04:52.350 --> 01:04:56.840
But at a place like Di Fara, the
best method is you go in,

01:04:56.840 --> 01:04:58.320
and you look down
at the counter.

01:04:58.320 --> 01:04:59.900
And sometimes, there's
a slice pie.

01:04:59.900 --> 01:05:00.910
And sometimes, there are slices

01:05:00.910 --> 01:05:02.230
there that are unclaimed.

01:05:02.230 --> 01:05:03.760
Jump on that, and then put your

01:05:03.760 --> 01:05:06.130
order in for the opposite.

01:05:06.130 --> 01:05:08.080
So if there's a round pie
sitting there, order a

01:05:08.080 --> 01:05:09.900
square whole pie.

01:05:09.900 --> 01:05:11.850
If there's a square sitting
there for slices, order the

01:05:11.850 --> 01:05:13.990
round whole pie, just so you
can get the best of both

01:05:13.990 --> 01:05:15.670
worlds, especially if you're
taking somebody there who's

01:05:15.670 --> 01:05:16.700
never been there before.

01:05:16.700 --> 01:05:17.470
You've got to jump on it.

01:05:17.470 --> 01:05:18.570
You've got to walk right in.

01:05:18.570 --> 01:05:20.930
And if you get there at 11:30,
they'll seat you.

01:05:20.930 --> 01:05:22.610
And they usually have
a pie ready to go.

01:05:25.210 --> 01:05:27.890
They're on top of it, although
they make it seem like they

01:05:27.890 --> 01:05:29.540
love drawing it out.

01:05:29.540 --> 01:05:33.642
It's just that he really just
won't move any faster.

01:05:33.642 --> 01:05:35.630
And you don't want him to,
